quran[45]{c,v,t}:
  53,26,And how many an Angel (there is) in the heavens whose intercession does not avail anything except even after Allah gives permission to whomever He decides and He is satisfied
  53,27,Surely the ones who do not believe in the Hereafter do indeed name the Angels with female naming
  53,28,"And in no way do they have any knowledge thereof. Decidedly they closely follow (nothing) except surmise, and surely surmise does not avail anything against the Truth"
  53,29,"So veer away from him who turns back from Our Remembrance and is not willing (to seek anything) except the present life (Literally: the lowly life, i.e., the life of this world)"
  53,30,"That is their attainment of knowledge. Surely your Lord is He Who knows best the ones who have erred away from His way, and He knows best the ones who are guided"
  53,31,And to Allah belongs whatever is in the heavens and whatever is in the earth that He may recompense the ones who have done odious (deeds) for what they have done and recompense the ones who have done fair (deeds) with the fairest reward
  53,32,"The ones who avoid the great (kinds) of vice and obscenities, except lesser offences; surely your Lord is Ever-Embracing in (His) forgiveness. He knows you best, as He brought you into being from the earth, and as you were embryos in your mothers' bellies; so do not (consider) yourselves cleansed; (only) He knows best him who is pious"
  53,33,Have you (The Prophet) then seen him who turns away
  53,34,And gives little and (then) parsimoniously
  53,35,"Does he have in his presence the knowledge of the Unseen, so he sees"
  53,36,Or even has he not been fully informed of what is in the Scrolls of Musa (Moses)
  53,37,"And Ibrahim, (Abraham) who constantly fulfilled the Message"
  53,38,That no encumbered self will be encumbered with the encumbrance of another
  53,39,And that man will have nothing except that for which he has endeavored (to achieve)
  53,40,And that his endeavor will eventually be seen
  53,41,(And) thereafter he will be recompensed for it with the fullest recompense
  53,42,"And that to your Lord is the final (End); (Or: judgment; recompense)"
  53,43,"And that He, Ever He, makes to laugh, and He makes to weep"
  53,44,"And that He Ever He, makes to die, and He makes to live"
  53,45,"And that He created the two pairs, the male and the female"
  53,46,From a sperm drop when it is ejaculated
  53,47,And that upon Him (rests) the other engendering
  53,48,"And that He, Ever He, enriches and gives property"
  53,49,"And that He, Ever He, is The Lord of Sirius; (Ash-Shicra, a star that was worshiped before Islam)"
  53,50,And that He caused to perish the earliest Aad
  53,51,And Thamud; so He did not spare (any of them)
  53,52,And the people of Nuh (Noah) earlier; surely they were the ones who were more unjust and more inordinate
  53,53,"And the City of Falsehood, He (also) made it sweep down"
  53,54,So that (there) He constantly enveloped it whatever He constantly enveloped
  53,55,Then whichever of your Lord's boons do you wrangle about
  53,56,"This is a Warner, of the earliest Warnings"
  53,57,TheImminent is imminent
  53,58,"Apart from Allah, none can lift it off"
  53,59,Do you then wonder at this discourse
  53,60,"And do you laugh, and do you not weep"
  53,61,(While) you amuse yourselves
  53,62,So prostrate yourselves to Allah and worship (Him).A prostration is to be performed here
  54,1,"The Hour (The Arabic noun is feminine) has drawn near, and the moon (The Arabic noun is masculine) is cloven"
  54,2,"And in case they see a sign, they veer away and say, \"A continuous sorcery"
  54,3,And they have cried lies and closely followed their prejudices; and every Command is settled
  54,4,And indeed there have already come to them such tidings wherein there is a scaring
  54,5,A consummate Wisdom; yet in no way do warnings avail
  54,6,So turn away from them. On the Day when the Caller will call to a highly maleficent thing
  54,7,"With most submissive be holdings, they will go out of the graves as if they were locusts spread abroad"
  54,8,"With their heads protruding, (hurrying) to the Caller. The disbelievers will say, \"This is a difficult Day"